<concept id="concept_f4v_hqm_mr">
 <title>Text Editor</title>
 <conbody>
  <p>The "Text Editor" tab is located in the upper part in the middle of the "Corpus" work space.
   The text input field is empty if no text from the Corpora is selected. Upon selecting the text
   you will be able to transliterate it and enter the hieroglyphs. This chapter provides a general
   description of the tab. For a step-by-step instruction of how to enter a new text please refer to
   the relevant <xref href="howto_edittext.dita">chapter </xref> in the "How-to" section of this
   manual. </p>
  <p>The "Text Editor" window contains two input fields. The upper one displays either
   "Transliteration", "Sign Text Editor" or "JSesh View" - depending on the tab selected. The lower
   input field displays translation of the sentence, selected in the upper window. </p>
  <p><b><u>Transliteration tab</u></b></p>
  <p>Here you can enter or modify the transliteration of the text. Be careful to follow the <xref
    href="howto_Grammatikfehler_e5.dita"/>, otherwise the autochecker system will trigger an error.
   The "Transliteration" tab is semantically connected to the <xref
    href="oberflaeche_lemmatizer.dita"/> tab below, where the transliterated words are referenced to
   individual lemmata. </p>
  <p><b><u>Sign Text Editor tab </u></b></p>
  <p>The "Sign-Text-Editor" tab provides the hieroglyphic version of the text. Initially only the
   transliteration is displayed there - each word / lemma in a separate box. The hieroglyphic input
   is done in the <image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/hieroglyphetw.png" id="image_ok5_nlw_nr"/>
   "Hieroglyph Type Writer" tab below. The hieroglyphic values, entered there, are automatically
   applied to the selected lemmata in the "Sign-Text-Editor" window. </p>
  <p><b><u>JSesh View</u></b></p>
  <p>Displays a cohesive hieroglyphic text. </p>
  <p>There are several buttons above the "Text-Editor" window: </p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/lemma-load.png" id="image_sws_dns_mr"/> "Load Lemmata of
   Text" loads the word borders and the sentence borders of your texts in order to be able to add a
   translation and to lemmatize the words in the next step.</p>
  <p>"Check Text Lemmata, Flexcodes..." checks the completeness of text lemmatization, translation
   and hieroglyphic transcription. </p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/annotation-add.png" id="image_ixh_g4s_mr"/> "Add
   Annotation" <xref href="howto_annotationen.dita">adds</xref> an <xref
    href="howto_annotationen.dita">Annotation</xref> to the selected part of your text. It will be
   underlined with a gray dotted line. </p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/rubrum-add.png" id="image_gwm_dqs_mr"/> "Add Rubrum"
   converts the active lemma into a rubrum, which is marked red in the text.</p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/subtext-add.png" id="image_zxr_pqs_mr"/> "Add
   Subtext/Glosse" adds a subtext or a gloss respectively as a "child" of your text. You can edit it
   separately.</p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/comment-add.png" id="image_d5g_krs_mr"/> "Add Comment"
   adds a comment to the selected part. It will be underlined yellow.</p>
  <p>You can use these functions also via the dropdown menu that appears when you click on the arrow
   on the right. </p>
  <p>Additionally, for Annotations, Rubra and Comments, a small, rectangular bar will appear on the
   right side of the Text-Editor with the corresponding colour. Clicking on the bar will bring you
   to the marked fragment of the text. </p>
  <p><b><u>"Sentence translation" text input field</u></b></p>
  <p>At the bottom of the "Text Editor" window there is the text-input field, where you can enter
   your translation. It is empty unless a lemma has been selected in the "Text editor" window.</p>
  <p>The <image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/locale.png" id="image_plt_3yt_mr"/> "Languages" icon
   offers a dropdown menu with a number of languages (English, German, French, Spanish, Russian) to
   choose from. Choose the language of your translation.</p>
  <p> </p>
 </conbody>
</concept>
